fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IDateTimeType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IType

    public interface IDateTimeType
extends IType
    Cell data type representing a date with time value. Values should be exchanged with the connector in the UTC time zone.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IDateType, ITimeType

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      boolean isLastModified()
      Indicates whether or not the associated date with time value defines an update timestamp that can be used as the last modification time of the associated item.

    • Method Detail

      • isLastModified

        boolean isLastModified()
        Indicates whether or not the associated date with time value defines an update timestamp that can be used as the last modification time of the associated item.

        The last modification field can be used for versioning and cache optimization.

        Returns:
        true if this field should be used to determine the time of the last modification applied to an item, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
